<apex:page standardController="Opportunity" extensions="ServiceAgreementController" renderAs="PDF" standardStylesheets="false" showHeader="false" applyBodyTag="false" applyHtmlTag="false" cache="true">
    <html>
        
        <head>
            <title>Change of Websites and merchant bank account</title>
            <style>
                @page {
                size: a4;
                
                @top-center {
                content: "";
                }
                @bottom-center {
                content: "Page " counter(page) " of " counter(pages);
                }
                }
                .page-break {
                display:block;
                page-break-after:always;
                }
                body {
                font-family: Arial;
                font-size: 14px;
                line-height: 20px;
                text-align:justify;
                padding-left:30px;
                padding-right:30px;
                }
                .table td{border:1px #000 solid!important;}
                .center-text{align:center;}
            </style>
        </head>
        
        <body>
            <div class="container">
                <p align="right">Date:&nbsp;<apex:outputText value="{0,date,MM'/'dd'/'yyyy}"><apex:param value="{!TODAY()}" /></apex:outputText></p>
                <p>To,</p>
                <p style="text-align:left;">
                    <strong>PayU Payments Private Limited,</strong>
                    <br/> 9th Floor, Bestech Business Tower,
                    <br/> Sohna Road, Sector-48, Gurgaon,
                    <br/> Haryana, Pin Code-122002
                    <br/>
                </p>
                <p>Dear Sir,</p>
                <p><strong><u>Subject: Change of Website and Merchant Bank Account</u></strong></p>
                <p><strong>{!accObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong>, a {!accObj.Business_Entity__r.Name}, entered into an Agreement with PayU Payments Private Limited (<strong>"PayU"</strong>) in accordance to which PayU provides us with aggregate online payment gateway solutions and services through its 'PayU' platform (<strong>"PayU Services"</strong>) for our website domain name:<strong>{!oppObj.Website__c}</strong>.</p>
                <p>We would like to inform you that we have changed our Website domain from:</p>
                
                <table width="80%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse;">
                    <tr>
                        <td width="50%">Old Website Domain</td>
                        <td width="50%">{!IF(oppParentObj.Id != null && oppParentObj.Website__c != null, oppParentObj.Website__c, null)}</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <p><strong>To:</strong></p>
                <table width="80%" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse;">
                    <tr>
                        <td width="50%">New Website Domain</td>
                        <td width="50%">{!oppObj.Website__c}</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <p><strong>And</strong></p>
                <p>We would like to change our Merchant Bank Account (as defined in the Service Agreement), in which the Customer Charge minus the TDR (<strong>"Settlement Amount"</strong>) payable to us is settled by PayU under the terms of Service Agreement.</p>
                
                <table  width="100%" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" border="1" style="border-collapse: collapse;">
                    <tr>
                        <td align="center" colspan="2"><strong><u>New Merchant Bank Account Details For the New Website({!oppObj.Website__c})</u></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td width="50%"><strong><u>Particulars</u></strong></td>
                        <td width="50%"><strong><u>Details</u></strong></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Bank Name</td>
                        <td>{!IF(lstBankAccDetail.size>0 && lstBankAccDetail[0].Bank_Name__c != null, lstBankAccDetail[0].Bank_Name__c, null)}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Bank Account No</td>
                        <td>{!IF(lstBankAccDetail.size>0 && lstBankAccDetail[0].Account_Number__c != null, lstBankAccDetail[0].Account_Number__c, null)}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Branch Address</td>
                        <td>{!IF(lstBankAccDetail.size>0 && lstBankAccDetail[0].Branch_Address__c != null, lstBankAccDetail[0].Branch_Address__c, null)}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>IFSC Code</td>
                        <td>{!IF(lstBankAccDetail.size>0 && lstBankAccDetail[0].IFSC_Code__c != null, lstBankAccDetail[0].IFSC_Code__c, null)}</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>Account Holder Name</td>
                        <td>{!IF(lstBankAccDetail.size>0 && lstBankAccDetail[0].Account_Holder_Name__c != null, lstBankAccDetail[0].Account_Holder_Name__c, null)}</td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
                <p>We request PayU to register and provide the PayU Services with respect to the new website domain herein mentioned above and discontinue all PayU Services with respect to Old website domain. We hereby confirm that the above mentioned website domain is owned and controlled by <strong>{!accObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong></p>
                
                <p>We understand that PayU may require certain documents in order to provide PayU Services with respect to the new website and the merchant account. We agree to provide the same as and when requested by PayU. We further understand that the change of the website domain to the Service Agreement and registration of the same will be subject to the approval by PayU.</p>
                <p>In addition, we acknowledge PayU will have to integrate the new website domain to PayU's Software Application and the change in the Merchant Account details will take effect only after the requisite change has been made in the records of PayU, Acquiring Banks and the Nodal Bank and this may take up to 5 Business Days from receipt of this letter and all such documents requested by PayU.</p>
                <p>We acknowledge that the submission of this letter will constitute as an amendment to the Service Agreement and any settlement Amount settled to our new merchant account and also any PayU Services provided on the new website will be governed by the terms and conditions of the Service Agreement.</p>
                <p>We hereby confirm that there has been no change in the legal name, registered office and/or constitution of <strong>{!accObj.Legal_Name__c}</strong> and/or the Authorized Signatory since the last application submitted to PayU.</p>
                
                <p>Best Regards,</p><br/>
                <p style="text-align:left;">__________________
                    <br/> <strong>Name:</strong>
                    <br/> <strong>Designation:</strong>
                    <br/> <strong>(Authorized Signatory)</strong>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>        
    </html>
</apex:page>